 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="4"><B><A NAME="tx294291_49"></A>ITEM&nbsp;2. ADVISORY VOTE TO APPROVE EXECUTIVE COMPENSATION
</B></FONT></P>  <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">In accordance with the Dodd-Frank Wall Street Reform and Consumer Protection Act of 2010 and related SEC rules, and consistent with our
shareholders&#146; preference as indicated at our 2011 annual meeting, our Board has adopted a policy of providing an annual shareholder vote to approve, on an advisory (non-binding) basis, the compensation of our Named Executive Officers as
disclosed in the proxy statement. </FONT></P>  <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">As described in detail under &#147;Compensation Discussion and Analysis,&#148; our executive compensation
programs are designed to attract, retain and motivate superior executive talent, including our Named Executive Officers, who are critical to our success. Under these programs, we seek to align pay and performance by making a significant portion of
our Named Executive Officers&#146; compensation dependent on: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">the achievement of specific annual and long-term strategic and financial goals; and </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">the realization of increased shareholder value. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">We have many compensation practices that ensure that our compensation programs are strongly aligned with our goals and strategies and promote good pay and
corporate governance practices. These practices are discussed in detail under &#147;Board Committees and Membership &#150; Human Resources and Compensation Committee&#148; and &#147;Compensation Discussion and Analysis&#148; and include: </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">we have substantial stock ownership guidelines and stock holding requirements for directors and executive officers that promote alignment of their interests with
our shareholders&#146; interests; </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">our long-term incentive program is 100% stock-based; </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">approximately 85% of our Chief Executive Officer&#146;s target total compensation is at-risk, incentive-based pay, of which over 70% is based on long-term
performance; </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">over 50% of our other Named Executive Officers&#146; target total compensation is based on long-term performance; </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">we do not pay the tax liability (i.e., no gross ups) associated with executive perquisites; </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">we employ our executive officers &#147;at will&#148; without individual severance agreements or employment contracts; and </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">we have significant risk mitigators, such as limits on incentive awards, use of multiple performance measures in our incentive plans, stock ownership and holding
requirements and an executive incentive compensation recoupment (clawback) policy. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>  <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Please read &#147;Compensation Discussion and
Analysis&#148; beginning on page 31 and &#147;Executive Compensation Tables&#148; beginning on page 55 for additional details about our executive compensation programs, including information about the fiscal year 2011 compensation of our Named
Executive Officers. </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">72 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">We are asking our shareholders to support our Named Executive Officer compensation as described in this Proxy
Statement. This proposal gives you, as a shareholder, the opportunity to express your views on our Named Executive Officers&#146; compensation. Your vote is not intended to address any specific item of our compensation program, but rather to address
our overall approach to the compensation of our Named Executive Officers described in this Proxy Statement. Our Human Resources and Compensation Committee and our Board believe our overall program effectively implements our compensation philosophy
and achieves our goals. Accordingly, we ask you to vote &#147;FOR&#148; the following resolution at our Annual Meeting: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">&#147;RESOLVED,
that Kraft Foods&#146; shareholders approve, on an advisory basis, the compensation paid to Kraft Foods&#146; Named Executive Officers, as disclosed in this Proxy Statement pursuant to the SEC&#146;s compensation disclosure rules, including the
Compensation Discussion and Analysis, the Executive Compensation Tables and related narrative discussion.&#148; </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><I>Required Vote: </I>Our Named
Executive Officer compensation as disclosed in this Proxy Statement will be approved if it receives more votes FOR than votes AGAINST. Abstentions and broker &#147;non-votes&#148; are not considered as votes cast with respect to this proposal and
therefore will have no effect on the outcome. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">This vote on the Named Executive Officer compensation is advisory, and therefore will not be binding on
Kraft Foods, our Human Resources and Compensation Committee or our Board. However, our Board and Human Resources and Compensation Committee value our shareholders&#146; opinions. If a significant percentage of our shareholders votes against the
Named Executive Officer compensation as disclosed in this Proxy Statement, we will consider our shareholders&#146; concerns, and the Human Resources and Compensation Committee will evaluate whether any actions are necessary or appropriate to address
those concerns. Unless our Board modifies its policy of holding an advisory vote to approve executive compensation on an annual basis, the next advisory vote will be held at our 2013 Annual Meeting of Shareholders. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>The Board recommends that you vote FOR the approval of our Named Executive Officer compensation as disclosed in this Proxy Statement. </B></FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">73 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="4"><B><A NAME="tx294291_50"></A>ITEM&nbsp;3. APPROVAL OF AN AMENDMENT TO THE AMENDED AND RESTATED ARTICLES
OF INCORPORATION TO CHANGE COMPANY NAME </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">On March&nbsp;14, 2012, the Board adopted a resolution approving an amendment to the Amended and Restated
Articles of Incorporation to change the name of our company and recommended that the amendment be submitted to shareholders for approval. The Board believes it is in the best interest of our company to change its name from Kraft Foods Inc. to
Mondel&#275;z International, Inc. and recommends the approval of the name change amendment to our shareholders. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>Reasons for Name Change
</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">On August&nbsp;4, 2011, we publicly announced the Spin-off. The Board believes it is best for the grocery business to retain the Kraft name by
becoming &#147;Kraft Foods Group, Inc.&#148; Kraft is an iconic name in the food business, especially in North America, where many of our company&#146;s products that will remain with Kraft Foods Group, Inc. have &#147;Kraft&#148; as a brand name or
endorser. </FONT></P>  <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Having allocated the Kraft Foods name to the new North American grocery company, the Board sought a name that would appropriately reflect
the nature and strength of the future global snacks business. It believes the name Mondel&#275;z International, Inc. does just that. &#147;Mondel&#275;z&#148; is a newly-created word that evokes the idea of a delicious world.
&#147;International&#148; expresses the global nature of the snacks business, and reinforces its key attributes: </FONT></P>  <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">It has an appealing, universal feeling </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">&#147;Monde&#148; derives from the Latin word for &#147;world&#148; </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">&#147;Del&#275;z&#148; is a fanciful expression of &#147;delicious&#148; </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Thus, the name has multiple, interrelated meanings that converge on &#147;delicious world&#148;&#150;a phrase the Board believes will serve as an umbrella for our iconic brands and build on our higher
purpose&#150;to &#147;make today delicious.&#148; </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Mondel&#275;z International, Inc. will be a corporate name. The Board does not envision using
&#147;Mondel&#275;z&#148; as a brand name. Changing the name of the company will not result in any change in the name of any branded consumer products that we market. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>Shareholder Action on the Name Change </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Shareholders are being asked to adopt the following resolutions:
</FONT></P>  <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4%;margin-right:8%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">&#147;Resolved, that the shareholders approve the amendment of ARTICLE I of the Corporation&#146;s Amended and
Restated Articles of Incorporation to read in its entirety as follows: </FONT></P>  <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">&#145;ARTICLE I </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">The name of the corporation is Mondel&#275;z International, Inc.&#146;; and further </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:4%;margin-right:8%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Resolved, that, notwithstanding the approval of the foregoing amendment, the Board of Directors of the Corporation may abandon the
amendment without further action by shareholders at any time prior to the time at which the amendment becomes effective.&#148; </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Subject to and following
shareholder approval of the amendment, we plan to cause the amendment to become effective by submitting Articles of Amendment to the Virginia State Corporation </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">74 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">
Commission. We may delay that submission until the Board of Directors gives final approval to the Spin-off. The amendment will become effective when the Virginia State Corporation Commission
accepts the Articles of Amendment and issues its Certificate of Amendment. The Board retains the right, without further shareholder action, to decide not to pursue the amendment at any time prior to it becoming effective, including, for example, if
the Spin-off does not occur. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">We have reserved the stock symbol &#147;MDLZ.&#148; If the name change amendment is approved, we intend to request that
the company&#146;s common stock trade under this new stock symbol, rather than under the current &#147;KFT&#148; symbol. The name change to Mondel&#275;z International, Inc. will not affect the validity or transferability of any currently
outstanding stock certificates and shareholders will not be requested to surrender for exchange any certificates presently held by them. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>Required
Vote for Approval </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Approval of the amendment to the Amended and Restated Articles of Incorporation to change the name of our company requires the
favorable vote of a majority of shares outstanding and entitled to vote. If you do not vote your shares, or you vote but abstain from voting on this item, it will have the effect of a vote <I>against </I>this proposal. Broker &#147;non-votes&#148;
also have the effect of votes <I>against </I>this proposal. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">If the name change amendment is not approved by shareholders, the proposed amendment to the
Amended and Restated Articles of Incorporation will not be made and our company&#146;s name and the ticker symbol for trading of its common stock will remained unchanged. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>The Board recommends a vote FOR the approval of the amendment to the Amended and Restated Articles of Incorporation of Kraft Foods Inc. to change the company&#146;s name to Mondel&#275;z International, Inc.
</B></FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">75 </FONT></P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="4"><B><A NAME="tx294291_51"></A>ITEM&nbsp;4. RATIFICATION OF THE </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="4"><B>SELECTION OF INDEPENDENT AUDITORS </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">The Audit
Committee is responsible for the selection, oversight, retention and termination of our independent auditors. The Audit Committee selected PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP, a registered public accounting firm, as our independent auditors for 2012.
PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP have been our independent auditors since 2001. The Audit Committee and the Board are requesting, as a matter of policy, that shareholders ratify the selection of PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP as our independent auditors.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">The Audit Committee and the Board are not required to take any action as a result of the outcome of the vote on this proposal. However, if our
shareholders do not ratify the selection, the Audit Committee may investigate the reasons for the shareholders&#146; rejection and may consider whether to retain PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP or appoint another independent auditor. Furthermore, even if
the selection is ratified, the Audit Committee may appoint a different independent auditor if, in its discretion, it determines that such a change would be in Kraft Foods&#146; and our shareholders&#146; best interests. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">We expect that representatives of PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP will be present at the Annual Meeting. They will have an opportunity to make a statement if they
desire to do so and to respond to appropriate questions from shareholders. Additional information about our independent auditors, including our pre-approval policies and PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP&#146;s aggregate fees billed for 2011 and 2010, can
be found above under &#147;Board Committees and Membership&#151;Audit Committee.&#148; </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>The Board recommends a vote FOR the ratification of the
selection of PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP as Kraft Foods&#146; independent auditors for 2012. </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="4"><B><A NAME="tx294291_52"></A>SHAREHOLDER
PROPOSALS </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">In accordance with SEC rules, we are including the following shareholder proposals (Items 5 through 7), along with the supporting
statements of the respective shareholder proponents. Kraft Foods is not responsible for any inaccuracies in these proposals and supporting statements. Each shareholder proposal is required to be submitted to a vote at the Annual Meeting only if
properly presented. <B>The Board recommendeds that you vote AGAINST each of these proposals for the reasons set forth in the Board of Directors&#146; Statement in Opposition following each proposal. </B> </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">The names, addresses and shareholdings of any co-filers of these proposals, where applicable, will be supplied upon request. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="3"><B><A NAME="tx294291_53"></A>ITEM&nbsp;5. Shareholder Proposal: Sustainable Forestry Report </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px;padding-bottom:0px;"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Domini Social Investments, 532 Broadway, 9</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="1"><SUP
STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex">th</SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"> Floor, New York, NY 10012, as manager of the Domini Social Equity Fund, beneficial owner of 344 shares of Kraft Foods&#146;
common stock, is the proponent of the following shareholder proposal and has advised us that a representative will present this proposal at the Annual Meeting. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>Whereas: </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Kraft is one of the world&#146;s largest consumer products companies, with a diversified line of
brands including Oreo, Nabisco and Oscar Mayer. Palm oil, soya, beef, sugar and paper are used in a variety of Kraft products. Globally, demand for these commodities is fueling deforestation. Several of these commodities have been linked to human
rights violations, including child and forced labor. </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">76 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Forests are rapidly declining at a rate of 55 football fields per minute according to the United Nations. Only about
20% of the world&#146;s original forests remain undisturbed. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">As a member of the Consumer Goods Forum, Kraft recognizes that &#147;Deforestation is one
of the principal drivers of climate change, accounting for 17% of greenhouse gases today. The consumer goods industry, through its growing use of soya, palm oil, beef, paper and board, creates many of the economic incentives which drive
deforestation.&#148; (Consumer Goods Forum press release, 11/29/10) </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">The Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change, the leading international network of
climate scientists, has concluded that global warming is &#147;unequivocal.&#148; The U.S. Environmental Protection Agency has determined that greenhouse gases threaten Americans&#146; health and welfare. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Climate change impacts from deforestation and poor forest management can be reduced through increased use of recycled materials, independent third party
certification schemes, and monitoring of supply chains. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Forest Footprint Disclosure (FFD), an initiative backed by more than 60 financial institutions
with over $6 trillion in assets under management, calls on global corporations to report on how their activities and supply chains contribute to deforestation and how those impacts are being managed. Although Kraft has received two annual requests
from FFD seeking disclosure of the company&#146;s management of deforestation risks in its supply chain, to date it has declined to respond. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Kraft&#146;s current sustainability report provides some indicators of how the company is managing deforestation risks, through purchases of certified Palm Oil and
reductions in packaging, for example. Proponent commends Kraft for these efforts. However, Kraft does not address the impact on forests of its soya, beef and sugar purchases. Several important indicators of how Kraft is managing deforestation risks
are lacking. These include: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">A company-wide policy on deforestation </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">The percentage of purchases of Palm Oil, beef, soya, sugar and paper that are sustainably sourced, with clear goals for each commodity
</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Identifying certification systems and programs that the company will use to ensure sustainable sourcing of each of these commodities.
</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Proponent believes that Kraft faces potential reputational and operational risks by failing to adequately disclose its approach to
managing deforestation risks. For example, Cadbury, now a Kraft brand, faced public controversy over use of Palm Oil in its Dairy Milk bars in New Zealand. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>RESOLVED</B>: Shareholders request the Board to prepare a report, at reasonable cost and omitting proprietary information, by December&nbsp;1, 2012, describing how Kraft is assessing the company&#146;s supply
chain impact on deforestation and the company&#146;s plans to mitigate these risks. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>BOARD OF DIRECTORS&#146; STATEMENT IN OPPOSITION TO THE PROPOSAL
</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>The Board recommends that you vote AGAINST this proposal for the following reasons: </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">At Kraft Foods, sustainability is a strategic global business priority. Our company conducts business in a way that respects the intersection of environmental, social and economic responsibility. Not only is this
the right thing to do; it makes good business sense. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">We share a great deal of information about our sustainability initiatives with shareholders and
other interested parties. For example, we outline our sustainability program &#150; our approach, our focus and our progress &#150; in an annual report called &#147;Creating a More Delicious World,&#148; which can be found on our website at
<U>http://www.kraftfoodscompany.com/DeliciousWorld/sustainability/index.aspx</U>. (Please note that the information in our website is not a part of this Proxy Statement.) </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">77 </FONT></P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Kraft Foods&#146;s sustainability initiatives focus on the six areas that matter most to our business and where we
believe our company can make the biggest difference. Those are: agricultural commodities; packaging; energy; water; waste and transportation/distribution. In each of these areas, we set goals and measure our progress, ensuring accountability and
real results. This has helped drive strong performance. For example, between 2005 and 2010, our: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">96&nbsp;million km (60 million road miles) have been removed from our company&#146;s transportation/distribution network. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">From a 2010 base, by the end of 2015 Kraft Foods plans to, among other things, increase sustainable sourcing of agricultural commodities by 25 percent and reduce
our direct water use by another 15 percent. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">At Kraft Foods, we believe that promoting sustainable farming improves crop yields, reduces environmental
impacts including deforestation, and generally helps to improve the lives of farm workers and their families. We are working, directly and through others, and investing millions of dollars to effect change in agricultural practices, particularly
where we are among the world&#146;s largest purchasers and where farming practices could be significantly improved. These commodities include: cocoa, coffee and cashews. We are currently expanding our efforts to other commodities such as sugar and
wheat. And we continue to work with the World Wildlife Fund (WWF), one of the world&#146;s largest conservation organizations, to better understand the risks associated with our purchases of agricultural commodities. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">More specifically, since a large portion of the crops we buy are threatened by circumstances such as political unrest, poor soil conditions and lack of
infrastructure, we believe it is important to address these challenges also by partnering with other companies, governments, non-governmental organizations, multilateral institutions, civil society and farmers themselves to create lasting change.
One example of a public-private partnership that Kraft Foods is co-chairing is the Word Economic Forum&#146;s New Vision for Agriculture (NVA) initiative. Begun in 2009, the NVA is simultaneously aiming at increasing food production, decreasing
carbon dioxide emissions and reducing poverty, in each case by 20 percent every decade. The NVA&#146;s projects are already delivering impressive results in several countries across Africa and Asia. We are also a partner in two initiatives led by a
private foundation that are investing $90 million over five years to advance sustainable production of cocoa and cashews in West Africa. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px;padding-bottom:0px;"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">In addition to these large partnerships, our company also uses third-party certification schemes to cultivate more responsible agricultural supply chains. We are one of the world&#146;s largest buyers of coffee
from Rainforest Alliance Certified</FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="1"><SUP STYLE="vertical-align:baseline; position:relative; bottom:.8ex">TM</SUP></FONT><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"> farms and the largest buyer of cocoa
beans from Fairtrade Certified or Rainforest Alliance Certified farms. As further described in the sustainability section of our company website, this support is making a difference in areas of Africa, Central America, South America and Southeast
Asia. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Important as these targeted initiatives are, they are not all we do. We work across our entire supply chain to reduce our footprint and improve
our sourcing of the raw materials we need to make our products. We have clear sourcing standards that all of our suppliers must meet. And we work with others to address specific concerns such as cocoa labor issues, palm oil-related deforestation and
animal welfare. For example, despite the relatively small quantities of palm oil that we purchase (less </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">78 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">
than 0.6 percent of worldwide production in 2011), we are working to purchase only palm oil certified by responsible third parties. Currently more than 50% of our palm oil purchases are covered
by GreenPalm certificates or certified palm oil. We expect to be able to cover 100 percent of our purchases once the supply of certified palm oil accounts for about one-third of the world&#146;s total supply, a goal we project to occur by 2015.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Kraft Foods is also a signatory of the Consumer Goods Forum (CGF) declaration on deforestation under which CGF member companies pledged to mobilize
their collective resources to help achieve zero net deforestation by 2020. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">In light of our existing efforts, accomplishments and reporting on
sustainable agriculture, the preparation of an additional report as requested by this shareholder proposal is unnecessary and not in our shareholders&#146; best interest. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>For the foregoing reasons, the Board recommends that you vote AGAINST this proposal. </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="3"><B><A NAME="tx294291_54">
</A>ITEM&nbsp;6. Shareholder Proposal: Report on Extended Producer Responsibility </B></FONT></P>  <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">As You Sow, 311 California Street, Suite 510, San Francisco,
CA 94104, as representative for Cedar Tree Foundation, beneficial owner of 9,800 shares of Kraft Foods&#146; common stock, is the proponent of the following shareholder proposal, &#147;Producer Responsibility for Packaging,&#148; and has advised us
a representative will present this proposal at the Annual Meeting. </FONT></P>  <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">WHEREAS product packaging is a significant consumer of natural resources and
energy, and a major source of waste and greenhouse gas (GHG) emissions. More than half of U.S. product packaging &#150; 37&nbsp;million tons &#150; is discarded in landfills or burned rather than recycled. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Packaging comprises nearly one-third of all U.S. landfill waste. Nestle Waters North America says plastic bottles are the largest contributor to its carbon foot
print; Coca-Cola Co. reports packaging is the largest part of the carbon footprint of several products. A recent analysis of U.S. Environmental Protection Agency data estimates that the energy needed to produce and dispose of products and packaging
accounts for 44% of total U.S. GHG emissions. Decaying paper packaging in landfills forms methane, whose greenhouse warming potential is 72 times more potent than CO2. Metal and plastic packaging has large embodied energy and emissions profiles
because of the high costs of producing those packages from mining/smelting and petroleum respectively. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Extended Producer Responsibility (EPR) is a
corporate and public policy that shifts accountability for collection and recycling from taxpayers and governments to producers. For instance, Coca-Cola, PepsiCo and Nestle Waters North America have each made public commitments to recycle a majority
of beverage containers sold over the next six to eight years. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">In many other countries, consumer packaged goods companies are responsible for
post-consumer packaging. Companies operating in Europe, Canada and Japan are required to pay some or all costs for packaging collection and recycling. More than half of Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development member countries have EPR
packaging systems in place. In Ontario, Canada, producers pay half of packaging collection and recycling costs. EPR programs in Austria, Belgium and Germany recover far higher rates of packaging than the U.S. EPR laws in 24 U.S. states already
mandate producer responsibility for collection and recycling of consumer electronics. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Producers control design and marketing decisions, and so are best
positioned to reduce the overall environmental impact of product packaging and internalize costs. Increased recycling of packaging can yield strong environmental benefits, leading to more efficient use of materials, reduced extraction of natural
resources, and fewer GHG and toxic emissions. EPR mandates can create new economic markets for packaging. Increased economic incentives to recycle more types of packaging will keep it from flowing into waterways and oceans where it imperils marine
life. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">79 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">BE IT RESOLVED THAT Shareowners of Kraft Foods request that the board of directors issue a report at reasonable cost,
omitting confidential information, by Sept. 1, 2012 assessing the feasibility of adopting a policy of Extended Producer Responsibility for post-consumer product packaging as a means of reducing carbon emissions and air and water pollution resulting
from the company&#146;s business practices, and increasing rates of packaging recycling; and describing efforts by the company to implement this strategy. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Supporting Statement: Proponents believe policy options reviewed in the report should include taking responsibility for post-consumer package recycling, and participating in development of producer financed and
managed EPR systems. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>BOARD OF DIRECTORS&#146; STATEMENT IN OPPOSITION TO THE PROPOSAL </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>The Board recommends that you vote AGAINST this proposal for the following reasons: </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">At Kraft Foods, we regard
sustainability as a strategic global business priority. We believe that sustainability is about conducting business in a way that is environmentally, socially and economically responsible. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">We outline our sustainability program in an annual report called &#147;Creating a More Delicious World,&#148; which can be found on our corporate website at
<U>http://www.kraftfoodscompany.com/DeliciousWorld/sustainability/index.aspx</U>. (Please note that the information in our website is not part of this Proxy Statement.) As explained in our Delicious World report, product packaging &#150; including
the design, production and post-consumer treatment of packaging &#150; is one of the six focus areas of Kraft Foods&#146; sustainability framework. We take a comprehensive approach to packaging &#150; one that cuts waste, conserves natural resources
and is satisfying to the end user. We set and meet goals. We are proud of our accomplishments to date and are committed to our goals for the future: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Between 2005 and 2010, we cut over 100,000 metric tons (200 million pounds) of packaging from our supply chain. We are working to eliminate another 50,000 metric
tons (100 million pounds) by 2015. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">We are working to incorporate more sustainable materials into our packaging. In North America, for example, the majority of people can recycle more than 70
percent (by weight) of our packaging. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">To increase recycling rates, we are using more recycled content in much of our packaging and partnering with others on education campaigns; and we are adding
statements to engage consumers such as &#147;Please Recycle This Carton&#148; to our packaging. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>  <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Kraft Foods&#146; sustainability
program is based on research and thoughtful design, focusing on areas that matter most to our business and where we believe our company can make the biggest difference. Our strategy reflects our belief in the efficacy of partnering with other
stakeholders including private, governmental and non-governmental organizations. We believe creating consumption patterns that are sustainable requires that everyone does their part: from individual consumers to private organizations to public
policymakers; and a lasting solution will require a comprehensive approach that includes public education, public-private partnerships, changes in public policy and the enhancement of infrastructure. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">We are involved in several initiatives around the world aimed at improving recycling rates, both at the company level as well as part of industry efforts. In the
U.S., we have been involved for several years with the Sustainable Packaging Coalition and the Grocery Manufacturers Association, with industry-wide collaborative efforts to address waste management across the lifecycle. In an ongoing effort to
drive global change in packaging, Kraft Foods also co-leads the Consumer Goods Forum&#146;s Global Packaging Project under which many of the world&#146;s largest consumer goods companies and major retailers have approved a suggested set of common
definitions and principles for packaging in the framework of sustainability. We are investing in new recycling technologies such as the Enval Consortium along with peer companies to enable higher recycling opportunities. </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">80 </FONT></P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Because we can demonstrate that our policies, practices and reporting are already moving us in the right direction, we
do not believe that a report on the adoption of an &#147;extended producer responsibility&#148; policy would be an effective use of our company&#146;s resources or in the best interest of our company or our shareholders. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>For the foregoing reasons, the Board recommends that you vote AGAINST this proposal. </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="3"><B><A NAME="tx294291_55"></A>ITEM&nbsp;7. Shareholder Proposal: Report on Lobbying </B></FONT></P>  <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">AFSCME Employees Pension
Plan, 1625 L Street, N.W., Washington D.C., 20036, beneficial owner of 12,460 shares of Kraft Foods&#146; common stock, is the proponent of the following shareholder proposal and has advised us a representative will present this proposal at the
Annual Meeting. </FONT></P>  <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>Whereas</B>, corporate lobbying exposes our company to risks that could affect the company&#146;s stated goals,
objectives, and ultimately shareholder value, and </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>Whereas</B>, we rely on the information provided by our company to evaluate goals
and objectives, and we, therefore, have a strong interest in full disclosure of our company&#146;s lobbying to assess whether our company&#146;s lobbying is consistent with its expressed goals and in the best interests of shareholders and long-term
value. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>Resolved</B>, the shareholders of Kraft Foods Inc. (&#147;Kraft&#148;) request the Board authorize the preparation of a
report, updated annually, disclosing: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

recipient of the communication to take action with respect to the legislation. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px; text-indent:4%"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Both &#147;direct and indirect lobbying&#148; and

the Audit Committee of the Board or other relevant oversight committees of the Board and posted on the company&#146;s website. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>Supporting Statement
</B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">As shareholders, we encourage transparency and accountability in the use of staff time and corporate funds to influence legislation and regulation
both directly and indirectly. We believe such disclosure is in shareholders&#146; best interests. Absent a system of accountability, company assets could be used for policy objectives contrary to Kraft&#146;s long-term interests. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Kraft spent approximately $6.39 million in 2009 and 2010 on direct federal lobbying activities, according to disclosure reports (<I>U.S. Senate Office of Public
Records)</I>. In 2010, according to </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">81 </FONT></P>

disclosure reports required in six states, Kraft also spent at least $548,436 on lobbying expenditures. These figures may not include grassroots lobbying to directly influence legislation by
mobilizing public support or opposition and do not include any lobbying expenditures to influence legislation or regulation in states that do not require disclosure. And Kraft does not disclose its contributions to tax-exempt organizations that
write and endorse model legislation, such as Kraft&#146;s $5,000 contribution to the American Legislative Exchange Council (&#147;ALEC&#148;) annual meeting </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT

<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">a list of all trade associations to which we pay annual dues greater than $50,000. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Our company has effective compliance procedures for, and oversight of, our corporate and Kraftpac political and lobbying activity. Our Code of Conduct requires us to deal honestly with the government. Our internal
compliance policies require advance business and legal approval of political contributions and lobbying activity. And, as you would expect, we file all information required by federal and state campaign finance and disclosure laws. All of these
filings are publicly available. In addition, the Board&#146;s Governance, Membership and Public Affairs Committee, which is charged with oversight of Kraft Foods&#146; policies and programs related to corporate citizenship, social responsibility,
and public policy issues significant to our company, including philanthropic and political activities and contributions, receives reports on our company&#146;s political and lobbying activities and discusses with management their strategies and
recommendations. Finally, we note: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">We do not fund &#147;independent expenditures.&#148; </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">We instruct that our dues paid to trade association groups cannot be used to support or oppose candidates &#150; only issues of importance to our company.
</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">We do not make political contributions to Presidential candidates; thus, our contributions are not connected to actions taken by federal regulators such as the
US Food and Drug Administration or the US Department of Agriculture. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">We do not support, directly or indirectly, candidates for judicial office. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">We have not made a &#147;grassroots lobbying communication&#148;, as defined by the proponent, since our company&#146;s inception as an independent company in
2007. </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Collecting and publishing the additional information requested by this proposal would be unnecessarily burdensome on company
resources and provide little, if any, new value to shareholders. We believe that our current disclosure, along with our internal compliance and oversight processes, is appropriate and in the best interests of our company and its shareholders.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>For the foregoing reasons, the Board recommends that you vote AGAINST this proposal. </B></FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">82 </FONT></P>

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="4"><B><A NAME="tx294291_56"></A>OTHER MATTERS THAT MAY BE </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="4"><B>PRESENTED AT THE ANNUAL MEETING </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">We do not
know of any matters, other than those described in this Proxy Statement, that may be presented for action at the Annual Meeting. If any other matters properly come before the Annual Meeting, your proxy gives authority to the persons named as proxies
in the proxy or voting instruction form to vote on these matters in accordance with their best judgment. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:24px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="4"><B><A NAME="tx294291_57"></A>FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS ABOUT THE ANNUAL MEETING AND VOTING </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>1.</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>When and where is the Annual Meeting? </B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">We will hold the
Annual Meeting on Wednesday, May&nbsp;23, 2012, at 9:00 a.m. CDT at the North Shore Center for the Performing Arts in Skokie, 9501 Skokie Boulevard, Skokie, Illinois 60077. The Center will open to shareholders at 8:00 a.m. CDT. Directions to the
Center are included at the end of this Proxy Statement. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>2.</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>Who is entitled to vote at the Annual Meeting? </B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">The Board
established March&nbsp;15, 2012 as the record date (the &#147;Record Date&#148;) for the Annual Meeting. Each shareholder (registered or beneficial) who held shares of our common stock at the close of business on the Record Date are entitled to
(a)&nbsp;receive notice of the Annual Meeting, (b)&nbsp;attend the Annual Meeting and (c)&nbsp;vote on all matters that properly come before the Annual Meeting. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">At the close of business on the Record Date, 1,772,061,678 shares of our common stock were outstanding and entitled to vote. Each share is entitled to one vote on each matter to be voted upon at the Annual Meeting.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>3.</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>Why am I receiving these proxy materials? </B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">In connection
with our Board&#146;s solicitation of proxies to be voted at the Annual Meeting, we are providing shareholders entitled to vote at the Annual Meeting with this Proxy Statement, our Form 10-K, our Chairman and Chief Executive Officer&#146;s letter to
shareholders and a voting ballot (in the form of a proxy card, voting instruction form, or a unique control number that allows you to vote via the Internet or by phone). We refer to these materials collectively as the &#147;proxy materials&#148;.
These materials provide important information about Kraft Foods and describe the voting procedures and the matters to be voted on at the Annual Meeting. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">You have received the proxy materials because, as of the Record Date, you directly or indirectly held, and had the right to vote, shares of Kraft Foods common
stock. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>4.</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>What is the difference between registered holders and beneficial holders? </B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">The most common ways in which shareholders hold Kraft Foods stock are: </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">directly with our transfer agent, Wells Fargo Bank, N.A. (<I>registered shareholders</I>); </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">indirectly through an account with an institutional or nominee holder of our stock such as a broker or bank who is the record holder of the stock (<I>beneficial
shareholde</I>r or <I>shareholder in street name</I>). </FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">If you hold your shares as a <I>registered shareholder</I>, our transfer agent
sends the proxy materials to you and your vote instructs the proxies how to vote your shares. </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">83 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">If you hold your shares in street name as a <I>beneficial shareholder</I>, your broker, bank or other nominee
delivers the proxy materials to you. Your vote instructs your nominee how to vote your shares, and that nominee in turn instructs the proxies how to vote your shares. If you hold your shares beneficially in an employee benefit plan, your shares are
voted by the trustee of the plan in accordance with the plan&#146;s governing documents and applicable law. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>5.</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>How is Kraft Foods distributing proxy materials? </B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>  <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">We are
furnishing proxy materials to our shareholders primarily via the Internet instead of mailing printed copies of proxy materials to each shareholder. On or about April 5, 2012, we mailed to our shareholders (other than those who previously requested
electronic or paper delivery) a Notice of Internet Availability of Proxy Materials (the &#147;Notice&#148;) containing instructions on how to access the proxy materials via the Internet. </FONT></P>  <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">If you receive a Notice by mail, you will not receive a printed copy of the proxy materials in the mail. Instead, the Notice instructs you on how to access the proxy materials via the Internet. The Notice also
instructs you on how you may submit your proxy vote via the Internet. If you received a Notice by mail and would like to receive a paper copy of our proxy materials on a one-time or ongoing basis, follow the instructions contained in the Notice for
making this request. The Notice also contains instructions on how you may request to receive an electronic copy of our proxy materials by email on a one-time or ongoing basis. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>We will send printed, paper copies of proxy materials, including our Form 10-K, free of charge to any shareholder who requests copies in writing to: Wells Fargo

<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>7.</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>What is the quorum requirement? </B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">A quorum of shareholders is
necessary to validly hold the Annual Meeting. A quorum will be present if a majority of the outstanding shares of our common stock entitled to vote as of the Record Date is represented at the Annual Meeting, either in person or by proxy. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">84 </FONT></P>

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Abstentions and broker non-votes will be counted for the purpose of determining whether a quorum is present for the
Annual Meeting. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>9.</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>What other matters may arise at the Annual Meeting? </B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Other
than Items 1 through 7 described in this Proxy Statement, we do not expect any matters to be presented for action at the Annual Meeting. The Chairman of the Annual Meeting may refuse to allow the presentation of a proposal or a nomination for the
Board at the Annual Meeting if it is not properly submitted. The requirements for shareholders to properly submit proposals and nominations at the Annual Meeting were described in our 2011 Proxy Statement. They are similar to those described under
&#147;2013 Annual Meeting of Shareholders&#148; in this Proxy Statement. If any other matters properly come before the Annual Meeting, your proxy gives authority to the designated proxies to vote on such matters in accordance with their best
judgment. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="5%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>10.</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>What vote is needed to elect directors? </B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Our By-Laws provide
that, to be elected at this Annual Meeting, a director nominee must receive more votes FOR than votes AGAINST. Abstentions and broker non-votes are not considered as votes FOR or votes AGAINST the nominees and will have no effect on the election of
directors. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Under our By-Laws and Guidelines and in accordance with Virginia law, in an uncontested election, if an incumbent director nominated for
re-election receives a greater number of votes AGAINST than </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">85 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">
votes FOR, the director must tender his or her resignation to the Governance, Membership and Public Affairs Committee for its consideration following certification of the election results. The
Governance, Membership and Public Affairs Committee then recommends to the Board whether to accept the resignation. The director will continue to serve until the Board decides whether to accept the resignation, but will not participate in the
Committee&#146;s recommendation or the Board&#146;s action regarding whether to accept the resignation offer. The Board will publicly disclose its decision and rationale within 90 days after certification of the election results. If the Board does
not accept the director&#146;s resignation, the director will continue to serve until the next annual meeting of shareholders or until the director&#146;s successor is duly elected and qualified. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">In contested elections, the voting standard is a plurality of votes cast. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>11.</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>What vote is needed to approve the other items? </B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B><I>Item&nbsp;3 &#150; Amendment to Amended and Restated Articles of Incorporation </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Approval of the amendment to the Amended and Restated Articles of Incorporation to change the name of the corporation requires the favorable vote of <U>a majority of shares outstanding and entitled to vote</U>. If
you do not vote your shares, or you vote but abstain from voting on this item, this has the effect of a vote <I>against</I>. Broker non-votes also have the effect of votes <I>against</I>. See Question 13 below for an explanation of &#147;broker
non-votes.&#148; </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B><I>Other Items </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Approval of
each of Item&nbsp;2 (Advisory Vote on Executive Compensation), Item&nbsp;4 (Ratification of the Selection of the Independent Auditors) and Items 5, 6 and 7 (Shareholder Proposals), requires the favorable vote of <U>a majority of votes cast</U>.
Abstentions and broker non-votes are not considered as votes cast and will have no effect on the matter. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
