<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>What are broker non-votes? </B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>  <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">As described above in
Question 4, if you hold your shares beneficially in street name, your vote instructs your broker, bank or other nominee, as the holder of record, how to vote your shares. Under </FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">86 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">
NYSE rules, if you do not provide voting instructions to your broker, bank or other nominee, your nominee has discretion to vote your shares on &#147;routine&#148; matters. The ratification of
the selection of the independent auditors (Item 4) is the only item on the agenda for the Annual Meeting that is considered routine. If you do not provide voting instructions and your nominee votes your shares, your shares will be counted toward the
quorum for the Annual Meeting and voted on Item&nbsp;4, but they will not be voted on the other items on the agenda, resulting in &#147;broker non-votes&#148; with respect to those other items. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>14.</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>I am a current/former Kraft Foods employee and have investments in the Kraft Foods Stock Fund(s) of the Kraft Foods Inc. Thrift/TIP 401(k) Plans(s) and/or the Kraft Foods
Canada Optional Pension Plan(s)/Employee Savings Plan. Can I vote? If so, how do I vote? </B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Yes, you are entitled to vote, and your
proxy card, or control number for voting electronically, includes all shares allocated to your Kraft Foods Stock Fund account(s). Your vote directs the plan(s) trustee(s) how to vote the shares allocated to your Kraft Foods Stock Fund account(s).
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">In order to direct the plan(s) trustee(s) how to vote the shares held in your Kraft Foods Stock Fund account(s), <U>you must vote these plan shares
(whether by Internet, telephone or mailed proxy card) by 11:59 p.m. CDT on Friday, May&nbsp;18, 2012</U>. If your voting instructions or proxy card are not received by that time, the trustee(s) will vote the shares allocated to your account(s) in
the same proportion as the respective plan shares for which voting instructions have been timely received, unless contrary to the Employee Retirement Income Security Act of 1974 (&#147;ERISA&#148;). Please follow the instructions for registered
shareholders described in Question 12 above to cast your vote. Note, however, that although you may attend the Annual Meeting, you may not vote shares held in your Kraft Foods Stock Fund account(s) at the meeting. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>15.</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>I am a Kraft Foods employee and hold shares of restricted stock. Can I vote my restricted stock holding? If so, how do I vote those shares? </B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Yes, you are entitled to vote, and your proxy card, or control number for voting electronically, includes any shares of restricted stock you may hold. If you hold
shares of restricted stock, you should follow the instructions for registered shareholders described in Question&nbsp;12 above to vote your restricted shares. <U>If you do not vote these shares, they will not be voted, so please vote</U>.
</FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>16.</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>How do I vote if I participate in Kraft Foods&#146; Direct Purchase Plan? </B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">If you hold shares in the Direct Purchase Plan, you should follow the instructions for registered shareholders described in Question 12 above to vote your shares. When you vote those shares, you will be voting all
the shares you hold at our transfer agent as a registered shareholder. <U>If you do not vote your shares, they will not be voted, so please vote</U>. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>17.</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>I hold Depository Interests (&#147;DIs&#148;) that represent entitlements to shares of Kraft Foods common stock as a result of Kraft Foods&#146; acquisition of Cadbury in
2010. Can I vote the shares of Kraft Foods common stock underlying my DIs? If so, how do I vote? </B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Yes, you can vote these shares
through the CREST electronic settlement system or by completing and sending a Form of Instruction, instructing the custodian for the Depositary Interest Service &#147;Computershare Company Nominees Limited&#148; to vote the shares of Kraft Foods
common stock at the Annual Meeting. Computershare will send all CREST participants (including nominee companies and sponsored individuals) that hold DIs a notice and Form of Instruction that allow these participants to attend and vote at the Annual
Meeting. If you are a CREST participant, you should either vote through the CREST system as shown on the Form of Instruction or by returning the Form of Instruction to Computershare by following the accompanying instructions. Computershare will then
arrange to vote your underlying shares of Kraft Foods common stock according to your instructions. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">87 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><I>If Computershare holds your DIs on your behalf within Kraft Foods Corporate Sponsored Nominee Service</I>,
Computershare, as the international nominee for your DIs, will send you a notice and Form of Direction. You may direct Computershare how to vote your underlying shares via the Internet or by returning your Form of Direction according to the
instructions in the notice and Form of Direction <U>by 11:59 p.m., London time, on Thursday, May&nbsp;17, 2012</U>, which is earlier than the voting deadlines listed above in Question 12. Computershare will then arrange to vote your underlying
shares according to your instructions. If you would like to attend and vote in person at the Annual Meeting, please inform Computershare, which will provide you with a letter of representation with respect to your DIs that will enable you to attend
and vote your underlying shares at the Annual Meeting on Computershare&#146;s behalf. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><I>If another international nominee holds your DIs on your
behalf</I>, your nominee may have its own arrangements in place to provide you with a separate notice of the Annual Meeting and proxy voting card with respect to your underlying shares. In that case, please follow your nominee&#146;s voting
instructions in that notice and proxy voting card to direct your nominee how to vote your underlying shares. Please vote by the deadline stated on the nominee&#146;s notice and proxy voting card, which is earlier than the voting deadlines listed
above in Question 12. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">If you hold DIs and have questions about voting your shares of Kraft Foods common stock underlying your CDIs, please contact
Computershare at <B></B>+44 (0)844 472 6005<B></B>. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>18.</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>May I change or revoke my vote? </B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Yes. If you are a
registered shareholder, any subsequent vote you cast will replace your earlier vote. This applies whether you vote by mailing a proxy card or by telephone or the Internet. You may also revoke an earlier vote by voting in person at the Annual
Meeting. Alternatively, you may revoke your proxy by submitting a written revocation to our Corporate Secretary at Kraft Foods Inc., Three Lakes Drive, Northfield, Illinois 60093. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">If you hold your shares in street name, you must contact your broker, bank or other nominee for specific instructions on how to change or revoke your vote. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>19.</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>Who bears the cost of soliciting votes for the Annual Meeting? </B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">We bear the cost of soliciting your vote. Our directors, officers or employees may solicit proxies or votes in person, by telephone or by electronic communication. They will not receive any additional compensation
for these solicitation activities. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">We will enlist the help of banks, brokers and other nominee holders in soliciting proxies for the Annual Meeting
from their customers (i.e., beneficial shareholders) and reimburse those firms for related out-of-pocket expenses. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">We retained Georgeson Inc. to aid in
soliciting votes for the Annual Meeting for a total fee of $14,000 plus reasonable expenses. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>20.</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>What is &#147;Householding&#148;? </B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Unless you advised
otherwise, if you hold your shares in street name and you and other residents at your mailing address share the same last name and also own shares of Kraft Foods common stock in an account at the same broker, bank or other nominee, your nominee
delivered a single Notice or set of proxy materials to your address. This method of delivery is known as householding. Householding reduces the number of mailings you receive, saves on printing and postage costs and helps the environment.
Shareholders who participate in householding continue to receive separate voting instruction cards and control numbers for voting electronically. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT SIZE="1">&nbsp;</FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">88 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">A shareholder who received a single Notice or set of proxy materials to a shared address may request a separate copy
of the Notice or proxy materials be sent to him or her by contacting Broadridge Financial Solutions, Inc. in writing to its Householding Department at 51 Mercedes Way, Edgewood, New York, 11717, or calling 1-800-542-1061. If you would like to opt
out of householding for future deliveries of proxy materials, please contact your broker, bank or other nominee. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Beneficial owners sharing an address
who are receiving multiple copies of the proxy materials and wish to receive a single copy of these materials in the future should contact their broker, bank or other nominee to make this request. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">If you are a registered shareholder or hold your share in an employee benefit plan, we sent you and each registered or plan shareholder at your address separate
Notices or sets of proxy materials. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>21.</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>Are my votes confidential? </B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Yes. Your votes will not be
disclosed to our directors, officers or employees, except (a)&nbsp;as necessary to meet applicable legal requirements and to assert or defend claims for or against us, (b)&nbsp;in the case of a contested proxy solicitation, (c)&nbsp;if you provide a
comment with your proxy or otherwise communicate your vote to us outside of the normal procedures or (d)&nbsp;as necessary to allow the inspector of election to certify the results. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>22.</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>Who counts the votes? </B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Wells Fargo Bank, N.A. will receive
and tabulate the proxies, and representatives of Wells Fargo Bank, N.A. will act as the inspectors of election and will certify the results. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR>
<TD WIDTH="6%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>23.</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>How do I find out the voting results? </B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">We expect to announce
preliminary voting results at the Annual Meeting. We will disclose the final voting results in a Current Report on Form 8-K to be filed with the SEC on or before May&nbsp;30, 2012. The Form&nbsp;8-K will be available at
<I><U>www.kraftfoodscompany.com/investor/sec-filings-annual-report</U></I> and&nbsp;on&nbsp;the&nbsp;SEC&#146;s website at <I><U>www.sec.gov</U>.</I> </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="6%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>24.</B></FONT></TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>What do I need to do if I would like to attend the Annual Meeting? </B></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">If you would like to attend the Annual Meeting, please pre-register by 11:59 p.m. CDT on Sunday, May&nbsp;20, 2012. Due to space limitations, you may bring only one guest. If you wish to bring a guest, you must
indicate that when you pre-register. <B>You and your guest, if any, must present valid government-issued photographic identification, such as a driver&#146;s license, to be admitted into the Annual Meeting</B>. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">If you are a registered shareholder, please indicate that you intend to attend the Annual Meeting by: </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="4"><B><A NAME="tx294291_58"></A>2013 ANNUAL MEETING OF SHAREHOLDERS </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">We presently anticipate that the 2013 Annual Meeting of Shareholders will be held on approximately the same date as this year&#146;s Annual Meeting. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B><A NAME="tx294291_59"></A>Shareholder Nominations and Proposals for the 2013 Annual Meeting </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Under our By-Laws, a shareholder may nominate a candidate for election as a director or propose business for consideration at an annual meeting of shareholders by delivering written notice that contains certain
required information to our Corporate Secretary. We must receive this written notice no later than 120 days, and no earlier than 150 days, before the first anniversary of the preceding year&#146;s annual meeting. Accordingly, to be considered at the
2013 Annual Meeting of Shareholders, our Corporate Secretary must receive a shareholder&#146;s written notice of nomination or proposal on or after December&nbsp;24, 2012 and on or before January&nbsp;23, 2013. If we change the date of an annual
meeting by more than 30 days from the date of the previous year&#146;s annual meeting, then we must receive this written notice no later than 60 days before the date of the Annual Meeting. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Under SEC Rule 14a-8, a shareholder may submit a proposal for possible inclusion in a proxy statement for an annual meeting of shareholders by submitting the proposal and other required information to our principal
executive offices. We must receive the proposal no later than 120 calendar days before the one-year anniversary date of our Proxy Statement for the previous year&#146;s annual meeting. Accordingly, to be considered for inclusion in our 2013 Proxy
Statement, we must receive a shareholder&#146;s submission of a proposal on or before the close of business on December&nbsp;3, 2012. If we did not hold an annual meeting the previous year, or if we change the date of an annual meeting by more than
30 days from the date of the previous year&#146;s annual meeting, then the deadline is a reasonable time before we print and send our proxy materials for the annual meeting. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Shareholders should mail all nominations and proposals to our Corporate Secretary at Kraft Foods Inc., Three Lakes Drive, Northfield, Illinois 60093. You may obtain a copy of our By-Laws from our Corporate
Secretary by written request to the same address. Our By-Laws are also available on our website at <I><U>www.kraftfoodscompany.com/investor/corporate-governance</U></I>. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:18px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>

</TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>From the North: (Wisconsin, northern suburbs) </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Take I-94 east, exit at Old Orchard Rd. Turn left onto Old Orchard Rd. going east. At Skokie Blvd., turn right going south. Take Skokie Blvd. south approximately 4 blocks. Westfield (Old Orchard) Shopping Center
will be on your right side. Turn left at the light just after Golf Rd. The North Shore Center for the Performing Arts is located between the Doubletree Hotel and Old Navy. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>From the South: (Chicago, I-55, south suburbs) </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Take I-94 west, exit at Old Orchard Rd. Turn right onto Old
Orchard Rd. going east. At Skokie Blvd., turn right going south. Take Skokie Blvd. south approximately 4 blocks. Westfield (Old Orchard) Shopping Center will be on your right side. Turn left at the light just after Golf Rd. The North Shore Center
for the Performing Arts is located between the Doubletree Hotel and Old Navy. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>From the West: (West suburbs, I-88, I-90) </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Take I-294 north, exit at Dempster St. east. Take Dempster east to Gross Point Rd. Turn left. Take Gross Point Rd. to Skokie Blvd. Turn left. Turn right at the
second light which is Foster St. The North Shore Center for the Performing Arts is located between the Doubletree Hotel and Old Navy. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>From
Schaumburg, Arlington Heights, Rolling Meadows and other Northwestern suburbs: </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2">Take Golf Rd. east until you reach Skokie Blvd. Turn right on Skokie
Blvd. and immediately get into the left lane. Turn left at the next light, which is Foster St. The North Shore Center for the Performing Arts is located between the Doubletree Hotel and Old Navy. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:arial" SIZE="2"><B>Parking attendants will direct attendees to the appropriate parking areas on-site. </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>  <P STYLE="margin-top:6px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g294291g62b92.jpg" ALT="LOGO">

<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">The shares of stock you hold in your account or in a dividend reinvestment account will be voted as you specify on the reverse side. </FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>If no choice is specified, the proxy will be voted &#147;FOR&#148; Items 1, 2, 3 and 4 and &#147;AGAINST&#148; Items 5, 6 and 7. </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">By signing the proxy, you revoke all prior proxies and appoint Carol J. Ward and Phuong Lam and each or either of them with full power of substitution,
to vote your shares on the matters shown on the reverse side of this card and any other matters which may come before the Annual Meeting or any postponements or adjournments thereof. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">In addition, if you are a current or former Kraft Foods employee and have investments in the Kraft Foods Stock Fund(s) of the Kraft Foods Inc. Thrift/TIP 401(k) Plan(s) and/or the Kraft Foods Canada
Optional Pension Plan(s)/ Employee Savings Plan on March 15, 2012, you are directing the plan(s) trustee(s) how to vote the shares allocated to your account(s). If your voting instructions are not received by 11:59 p.m. CDT on May 18, 2012, as
described in the Proxy Statement, the trustee(s) will vote the shares allocated to your Kraft Foods Stock Fund account(s) in the same proportion as the respective plan shares for which voting instructions have been received, unless contrary to the
Employee Retirement Income Security Act of 1974 (ERISA). </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:24px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>Vote by Internet, Telephone or Mail </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2"><B>24 Hours a Day, 7 Days a Week </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">Your Internet or phone vote authorizes the named proxies to vote your shares </FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman" SIZE="2">in
the same manner as if you marked, signed and returned your proxy card. </FONT></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12px;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:0px">&nbsp;</P>
